http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0079815/&lt;/a&gt;

A little warning: Jamaican english, especially creole and rastafarian, is one of the most extreme english accents there is. Fortunatly it&amp;#039;s subtitled most of the time but it&amp;#039;s not translated to british/american english, it&amp;#039;s subtitled in the original jamaican rastafarian english. You&amp;#039;ll understand 99% of what they say (by reading the subtitles) if you read this page before watching it:
